EDIT:  
@wizard\_pick - If a spell is green **AND** one of the listed colors (also known as a two color spell), then it will trigger. Example: [Watchwolf](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Watchwolf) will trigger Quirion Dryad.  

@ghostphoenix - yes, that is true. Quirion Dryad will trigger whenever you cast a White, Blue, Black, or Red spell. The spell does not have to resolve in order for Quirion Dryad to get the +1/+1 counter.

If you cast a card that is both red and white (eg. [Boros Recruit](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Boros Recruit)) does the Dryad's ability trigger twice?  

@ghostphoniex  
I believe that that is the case, the +1/+1 counter will go on the dryad before the spell resolves (or is countered) so it should also work for cards that rely on the power of a card (eg. [swords to plowshares](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=swords to plowshares)).

